node.text: “Do what is right for you. Do it over and over again. Lean into the light. Keep going even when it is hard. Especially when it is hard. Do not let doubt stop you. Trust the process even when your mood is low. Let growth be your mission. Let healing be your reward. Let freedom be your goal.” - @yung_pueblo

node.text:
“Whenever you start to doubt your strength again, remember what this journey looked like when you first began. You did not know it all, you did not feel strong, but you kept on believing yourself through it all. It was hard to keep going at time but breath by breath, step by step, you have come this far. Even if right now life is still full of uncertainty and stress, know that it is okay, in your own time you will overcome them.” 🧡
caption: @poetryofdhiman

node.text:
Affirmation of the Day: I have the ability to make progress, with ease, today. I have plenty of time when I decide to tackle things one thing at a time. I release all negative attachments, thoughts and feelings that are blocking me from receiving and blocking my path. I move forward with confidence and no longer press rewind. 🧡
#healing #affirmations

node.text:
#ad @VSPINK’s “Back to ____” campaign is all about reminding us to focus on what is important and being intentional about doing what is best for our mental health. To celebrate, they’re donating $200,000 to @JedFoundation’s Set to Go program. This initiative works online and on campus to help students and their parents manage the transition to college, emphasizing mental health and wellness.
 
Additionally, @VSPINK is back to in-person events! For their latest series, they are popping up across the U.S. and have created a safe space for you to relax, reflect, then share what you’re excited to get back to this year. In support of this initiative, we joined forces with PINK to create an adult coloring book and activity journal filled with some of your favorite WE THE URBAN quotes and plenty of space to write your feelings. Gather your friends & get the journal exclusively at the remaining dates below.
 
11am - 7pm each day
-
Atlanta – Atlantic Station
1380 Atlantic Dr, Atlanta, GA 30363
August 19-21
 
Tampa – Sparkman Wharf
615 Channelside Dr, Tampa, FL 33602
August 26-28
 
#PINKBackToYou

node.text: Affirmation of the Day: I will focus on my progress over perfection. I know that progress may sometimes be painful, other times beautiful, but it’s always powerful and necessary. I don’t know what the future holds, but I affirm that it is far greater than anything I can imagine. I am at peace with my pace. I am on my way and becoming better with each new day. 🧡

node.text:
“In order to make a relationship last, you really have to flow with a person as they change. Give them space. My friend always told me about his grandfather who was with his wife for 60 years before she passed. His grandfather said that through all that time, his wife changed so much it felt like he had been with 8 different people by the end. But he said the secret to making it last was that through all those changes, he never suffocated his wife with his own idea of who he expected her to be. Rather he loved, fully, every new woman she became.” 🧡
